Athletics doping: Russia could be suspended from IAAF - Lord Coe
Media playback is not supported on this deviceIAAF president Lord Coe says Russia could face sanctions and even suspension from athletics' world governing body.Lord Coe's comments followa World Anti-Doping Agency commission reportexamining allegations of doping, cover-ups, and extortion in Russian athletics.He told BBC sports news correspondent Richard Conway the findings had been a surprise and that "the scale and depth of the allegations is truly shocking".